      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOUBLE LOU (7) was first up for 10 weeks when he came from a similar barrier to be beaten 1.8m into second at Menangle a fortnight ago, continuing a run of wins and placings from last campaign. Has recorded a win and two placings in three second-up attempts so should be improved. Can go one better. SUGAR PIE HONEY (6) is a capable mare who found form in recording back-to-back Menangle wins before a fifth in a Listed race for the mares last time. She can make an impact if things go her way. BIRKIRKARA (3) worked from a tough barrier last week but draws much better and was racing consistently prior so is worth another chance. CALL TO ORDER (8) came from a 10m handicap to place in the Redcliffe Cup consolation last week and was midfield in the Flashing Red here prior. Draws for a trail so can be competitive. CYA ART NZ (9) placed in last year's Inter Dominion final here so his best form would measure right up.",
